From 7cea725d44d061a0b8585d654f1c6b8e83c2a263 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: NelloKudo <marshnelloosu@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 8 Mar 2026 22:17:49 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 10/11] win32u: Fix NtUserEnableMouseInPointer to respect the
 enable parameter.

Uma Musume (JP) stopped working after the following commits: https://github.com/ValveSoftware/wine/compare/6bf56848cca47a33c4ec7e545e38f7c519d1a890...92e7a733b1c8e5cfea648902066f8798fa39c50f.

Tracing why the game worked before them, it seemed to be due to the POINTER_MESSAGE_FLAG_PRIMARY that used to be incorrectly
passed to process_mouse_message: after matching with Windows, the breakage resulted to be NtUserEnableMouseInPointer always passing TRUE instead of what the game engine actually wanted.
---
 dlls/win32u/input.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/dlls/win32u/input.c b/dlls/win32u/input.c
index 10390f83956..ed43a53a092 100644
--- a/dlls/win32u/input.c
+++ b/dlls/win32u/input.c
@@ -2729,7 +2729,7 @@ void toggle_caret( HWND hwnd )
 BOOL WINAPI NtUserEnableMouseInPointer( BOOL enable )
 {
     FIXME( "enable %u semi-stub!\n", enable );
-    enable_mouse_in_pointer = TRUE;
+    enable_mouse_in_pointer = enable;
     return TRUE;
 }
 
